post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text: Governor Greg Abbott announced today that all Texas schools will be closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. Although schools are closed, modified business operations and remote learning continues for our students and staff. Please stay tuned for more updates on how this will impact end-of-the-year events and other related topics.

SPIRIT WEEK begins tomorrow!
Manic Monday Morning – wear your pajamas to school
Toon Time Tuesday – dress as your favorite character
Wild WIFI Wednesday – dress as your favorite meme
Turn it up Thursday – dress in Calvin Nelms gear
Fun Face Friday – paint your face in a fun way – no masks!

All students must continue to follow dress code policies on these days. Students need to make sure their meme content and outfits are school appropriate at all times. Outfits are not allowed to be scary and no masks or anything covering the face are allowed.

✅ Summers, nights, and weekends off

post_text:
Our first six weeks has come to a close! :-) Here are a few reminders:

Report cards are coming home today.

PSAT payment deadline is Monday, October 10th. $10 for 8th/9th grades and $15 for 10th/11th grades. Money can be turned in to Mrs. Faulk during lunches.

Please remember that Monday, October 10th is a regular school day!

Thank you to all of you that came to visit last night at Open House! We thoroughly enjoyed getting to meet our new families and visit with our returning families! It was also a fun night to see our awesome middle school volleyball team win their game again! Good Job Girls!!!

post_text:
Can you believe the first six weeks ends today??? What a great start we have had!

A few upcoming events:

Open House is Wednesday, October 7th from 5-7pm.

Report Cards will go home on Thursday, October 8th.

PSAT for 10th & 11th Grades is October 14th.
PSAT for 8th & 9th Grades is October 15th. (Students will have a letter regarding the date change to bring home today.)

Texas A&M Field Trip is October 23rd. Sign ups for 11th and 12th grades will begin in about a week. 10th graders will be able to sign up if there is room available on the bus once 11th and 12th grade have signed up.

Have a great weekend!
